descript.abstract: Tax lots, right-of-way outlines and tax account numbers as represented on city tax assessor hard copy maps. Each Taxlot carries as an attribute the "Property ID" for that parcel which can be used to associate the taxlot with the information in the Assessor's database. Selected items from the Assessor's file are included in the attribute table for each taxlot. The tax lot spatial features are maintained by Neighborhood Development Services (NDS) staff. These taxlot parcels as well as the assessor data, are updated on a daily basis.
descript.purpose: All data associated with the taxlot data are compiled by the City of Charlottesville from existing records created and maintained by City Assessment and Taxation offices.Care should be taken in the use and interpretation of these data. Not all columns are fully populated by the assessor. For example, the landuse and property columns are maintained using GIS and are useful for producing generalized maps, but are not considered reliable for legal purposes. Field verification has not been done.
